{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"02df21dd-67ed-46ef-9313-26147d2feb70","content":"No files found in the working directory — I'll walk you through the conversion directly.\n\n## Converting to Compiled Bindings\n\nAdd `x:DataType` to your `ContentPage` element, pointing at your ViewModel:\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\">\n\n    <VerticalStackLayout Padding=\"20\" Spacing=\"15\">\n\n        <Picker Title=\"Theme\"\n                SelectedItem=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n\n        <HorizontalStackLayout Spacing=\"10\">\n            <Label Text=\"Notifications\" VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n            <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n        </HorizontalStackLayout>\n\n        <HorizontalStackLayout Spacing=\"10\">\n            <Label Text=\"Font Size\" VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n            <Stepper Value=\"{Binding FontSize}\" Minimum=\"8\" Maximum=\"36\" Increment=\"1\" />\n            <Label Text=\"{Binding FontSize, StringFormat='{0}pt'}\" />\n        </HorizontalStackLayout>\n\n    </VerticalStackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nThe **only structural change** is adding `x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"` — every `{Binding}` under that scope is now compiled.\n\n## How it catches errors at build time\n\nWith `x:DataType` set, the XAML compiler resolves bindings **at compile time** against the declared type. If you typo a property name (e.g., `{Binding Themes}` instead of `{Binding Theme}`), you get a **build error** like:\n\n```\nXC0045: Binding: Property \"Themes\" not found on \"SettingsViewModel\".\n```\n\n## Key things to know\n\n| Topic | Detail |\n|---|---|\n| **Scope** | `x:DataType` cascades to all children; you can override it on any nested element |\n| **Opt out locally** | Use `x:DataType=\"\"` (empty string) on a subtree that needs classic reflection bindings (e.g., binding to `BindingContext` itself) |\n| **Performance** | Compiled bindings skip runtime reflection — they're faster and allocate less |\n| **Requirement** | The target type must be known at compile time; it won't work with `object` or `dynamic` |\n\nNo runtime surprises — property mismatches, type mismatches, and missing properties all become **compile-time errors**.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ac5d4634-a027-4dc5-9db5-dd0405edbad8","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"No files found. The user is asking a conceptual question about converting a MAUI page to use compiled bindings. Let me provide guidance on how to do this.\n\nSince there are no actual files, I'll explain the conversion process clearly.","outputTokens":729,"requestId":"9BD2:11AB75:61F667A:6D1FB24:69EC0E29"},"id":"efe27abe-3466-4525-97b3-47f650166e0e","timestamp":"2026-04-25T00:43:35.322Z","parentId":"82255358-117d-4779-9fc5-8f53880f6c72"}
